# Layout Decision Gate

When implementing a new feature page or modifying an existing page, you must first confirm the layout.

Before writing code, read:

- AGENTS.md
- specs/INDEX.md
- specs/layout-structure.md
- specs/pages.md if route/page mapping is involved

You must output a `Layout Decision` section before code.

The Layout Decision must include:

1. route type:
   - dashboard route: app/[lang]/(dashboard)/*
   - standalone route: app/[lang]/*
   - shared route group layout

2. selected page template:
   - WorkspaceDashboardTemplate
   - DataManagementTemplate
   - AgentWorkspaceTemplate
   - ExecutionDetailTemplate
   - DocumentWorkspaceTemplate
   - SettingsTemplate
   - Custom, only if justified

3. shell inheritance:
   - whether it inherits Header
   - whether it inherits Sidebar
   - whether it inherits Footer
   - whether it inherits ThemeCustomize
   - whether it inherits Auth protection

4. layout files:
   - whether page.tsx only is enough
   - whether page-level layout.tsx is required
   - whether module-level WorkspaceLayout is required

5. Copilot behavior:
   - no Copilot page context
   - register page context only
   - AI three-column layout required
   - global Copilot sidebar only, do not create new provider

6. forbidden changes:
   - do not modify app/[lang]/layout.tsx
   - do not modify app/[lang]/(dashboard)/layout.tsx
   - do not modify provider/*
   - do not modify components/ui/*

Do not generate page code until this Layout Decision is present.
